channel.title: Is this power supply enough?
channel.description:
http://www.tigerdirect.com/applications/SearchTools/item-details.asp?EdpNo=4267964&Sku=ULT40312
It is an ultra x3 850 watt modular psu. I didn't go for the newer version because they fucked up the new modular cables and its $200. The thing is the reviews claim so problems so if you guys would look at it it would be great.
As you can see on the 12 volt rail the amps is only 55. While a comparable corsair unit has 80 amps on the 12 volt rail.
I plan to be running a single nvidia geforce gtx 465. Do you think this will have enough power for the single video card or do you think I should ditch the cosmetics and play safe with the corsair 850HX modular power supply?

item.title: Is this power supply enough?
item.dc:creator: @mwiebelhaus mwiebelhaus
item.description:
@mwiebelhaus wrote:

[quote=“xEnt, post:6, topic:344693”]http://www.tigerdirect.com/applications/SearchTools/item-details.asp?EdpNo=5074042&CatId=1483

thats much higher quality, cheaper and better for your use.[/quote]

See I was looking at that also, but don’t get me wrong. I have seen the ultra 600 modular supply used for 2 years with no problem. The main thing that makes me want to stick with the ultra is the way the connectors are set up, the fact that the 24 pin is also modular (black) looks nice on the motherboard and I really like cosmetics, but the quality of the supply (which really nobody knows) puts me in a deadlock. If they corsair would have made their 24 pin with black flex cord I would be happy, and if ultra wouldn’t have fucked up and made their x4’s without black flex cord I would have been happy. So currently I am awaiting a reply to my email I sent about seeing if I can get the black flex cord shipped with the newer x4 model but ethier their will be no reply, or they will say no.

In which case I will go with the HX850W rather than the HX650 because I wan’t to make sure I will have enough juice in case I do a new motherboard and SLI or crossfire.
